{
  "name": "ranger-attack",
  "extends": "../artbook.json",
  "_comment": "7-frame bow shot, rigged on the ranger-battle SKELETON (chest root, wide-brace legs, bow-arm holding the flipped bow forward, draw-arm pulling the string, nocked arrow, leaf-hood 3/4 head) instead of a slid flat body. The bow arm stays braced on the target while the DRAW arm hauls the string back on a slow held aim (the tension), then the string snaps forward on a single fast frame and the arrow leaves. Weight reads through the draw (lean back onto the rear leg) and the release recoil (drive forward). The loosed arrow crosses the frame in wide jumps so it reads as fast. Facing right.",
